public class OclReplacerVisitor
extends org.eclipse.ocl.utilities.AbstractVisitor<java.lang.String,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Classifier,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Operation,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.EnumerationLiteral,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Parameter,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.State,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.CallOperationAction,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.SendSignalAction,org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Constraint>

Visits an OCL expression and replaces occurrences of modified variables by the name of the variable that holds its current value Example : Variable x, in behavior B0, if x has been modified 3 times all occurrences of x will be replaced by x_B0_3
